# Synonym Roll Design Rules & UI/UX Guidelines

## 🎯 **Core Design Philosophy**

### **Wordle-Inspired Aesthetics**
- Clean, minimalist interface that prioritizes content over decoration
- High contrast text and backgrounds for optimal readability
- Consistent spacing and typography throughout the application
- Focus on the word tiles as the primary interactive elements

### **Daily Word Game Principles**
- **Accessibility First**: Ensure all users can play regardless of ability
- **Progressive Disclosure**: Show information when needed, hide complexity
- **Immediate Feedback**: Clear visual responses to user actions
- **Consistent Patterns**: Predictable interactions across all game elements

## 🎨 **Visual Design System**

### **Color Palette & Theming**

#### **Light Mode (Default)**
```css
/* Primary Colors */
--color-primary: #5c62d6;           /* Main brand color */
--color-primary-light: #8287e0;    /* Lighter variant */
--color-primary-dark: #4a4fc7;     /* Darker variant */

/* Text Colors */
--color-text-primary: #333333;     /* Main text */
--color-text-secondary: #666666;   /* Secondary text */
--color-text-inverse: #ffffff;     /* Text on dark backgrounds */

/* Background Colors */
--color-background-light: #ffffff;     /* Main background */
--color-background-medium: #f8f9fa;    /* Card backgrounds */
--color-background-dark: #e9ecef;      /* Subtle backgrounds */
```

#### **Dark Mode**
```css
/* Primary Colors (Inverted) */
--color-primary: #fefdf8;          /* Light primary */
--color-primary-light: #f8f4ea;    /* Lighter variant */
--color-primary-dark: #c19a6b;      /* Darker variant */

/* Text Colors */
--color-text-primary: #f1dfc9;     /* Light text */
--color-text-secondary: #d5c7b2;  /* Muted text */
